snippet.textDisplay: Out of context, a lot of the jokes seem like immature potty humor. But it's really just the dressing on the show as a whole. You need to watch an episode or 2 to really understand why people love it so much. Pickle Rick is hilarious but out of context it's just a random guy who turns himself into a pickle for seemingly no reason. Kinda does the show more of a disservice to just show snippets like that without knowing a little more about the context. Rick and Morty is a lot more subtle with it's messages and themes than show's like Simpsons and South Park, but a lot more brunt with the "potty humor" at times because of Ricks cynical nihilistic nature.
